        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "View helper url(): in my opionion reset flag set to false by default is OK but only if preserved params are only: module, controller and action. Generation of new url using some custom params from current URL (customerId, etc...) doesn't make much sense for me. \n\nExample: after browsing page customer\/view\/customerId\/3, I click in menu on url('action' => 'add') and I get this customer\/add\/customerId\/3 ..  \nThis should not happen by default...\n\n"
        },
